Description
Read More


Collect the 3 Inch John W. Snow Secretary of the Treasury Bronze Medal featuring an obverse design with a portrait of Secretary Snow with the inscriptions “JOHN W. SNOW” and “73rd SECRETARY OF THE TREASURY.”
The reverse depicts a symbolic heraldic American eagle clutching olive leaves in one claw and arrows in the other, representing strength and confidence. The design also depicts a shield, which is based on the Department of the Treasury Seal. The inscriptions “THE DEPARTMENT OF THE TREASURY,” “UNITED STATES OF AMERICA,” “E PLURIBUS UNUM” and “IN GOD WE TRUST” also appear on the reverse.


Read Less
Specifications
Read More


Product Specifications


Design:
Obverse – Donna Weaver
Reverse – Don Everhart


Struck Under Authority of:
31 U.S.C. § 5111(a)(2)


Place Minted:
Philadelphia Mint (no mint mark)


Composition:
90% Copper & 10% Zinc




